{
  "texts": [
    "10.3389/fpsyg.2024.1382693 Frontiers in Psychology 06 frontiersin.org 4.1.2 Familiarity and self-efficacy",
    "An individual's familiarity with AI, rooted in their knowledge and prior interactive experience, plays a pivotal role in trust formation (Gefen et al., 2003).",
    "Such familiarity not only reduces cognitive complexity by supplying essential background information and a cognitive framework, but also enables the formation of concrete expectations regarding the AI's future behavior (Gefen, 2000).",
    "Additionally, a deeper understanding of AI can reduce the perceived risks and uncertainties associated with its use (Lu et al., 2019).",
    "Relatedly, AI use self-efficacy, or individuals' confidence in their ability to effectively use AI, significantly influences acceptance and trust (REF)."
  ]
}